Preheat your #oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Remove the
@21 Day Aged British Rump Steaks{2} from your fridge to allow them to
come up to room temperature.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into
1cm wide chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season
with @salt and @pepper, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single
layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch}(stalks and all).
Halve, peel and chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and chopped into
small pieces). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a
#garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of oil in a medium #frying pan{} on medium heat.

Once hot, add the shallot and cook until softened, ~{4-5%minutes}, then
add the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds} more.

Pour in the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and allow it to evaporate, ~{30%seconds}.

Add the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{100%ml} to the pan. Bring
to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer for ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir through the @butter{30%g} until melted. Simmer until thickened,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Remove from the heat and cover with a #lid to keep warm.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large frying pan on high heat. Season the
steaks with @salt and @pepper.

> TIP: Rump steaks naturally vary in shape, so adjust the following
> timings depending on how you like yours cooked.

Once very hot, lay the steaks into the pan and fry until browned and
medium-rare, about ~{5%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

> TIP: Cook each side for 1 min more if you like it more well done.

Once cooked, transfer the steak to a #board, cover with #foil and allow
to rest for a couple of minutes.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.
> The steak is safe to eat when browned on the outside.

When the chips have a few mins left, sprinkle over the
@grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} and return to the oven until
melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Wipe out the (now empty) steak frying pan, then return to medium-high
heat.

Once hot, add the @peas{120%g} and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}. Stir in
another knob of butter and season with @salt and @pepper.

When everything's ready, reheat your garlic butter sauce if needed and
stir through the parsley.

Transfer the rump steaks to your plates and serve the cheesy chips and
peas alongside.

Spoon the garlic butter sauce over the steaks to finish. Enjoy!